title: For Sale:  Browning Maxus
postcontent:
Bought New last year. Took it hunting a couple of times. Cleaned after every outing. 12ga 28" barrel. Awesome shotgun.
Description: Receiver - Strong, lightweight aluminum alloy
Barrel - Lightweight profile • Flat, ventilated rib
Action - Gas-operated autoloader • 3" and 3 1/2" chamber models • New Power Drive Gas System reduces recoil and cycles a wide range of loads 
Stock - Composite stock with close radius pistol grip • Speed Lock Forearm • Textured gripping surfaces • Mossy Oak® Duck Blind® camo finish • Dura-Touch® Armor Coating
Features - Vector Pro™ lengthened forcing cone • Three Invector-Plus™ choke tubes • Inflex Technology recoil pad • Lightning Trigger System • Magazine Cut-Off • Turnkey Magazine Plug

Camo finishes on today's modern firearms has nearly been perfected, if not perfect now. They adhere well, blend in perfectly with the intended surroundings and protect the gun from scratches, dings and the weather. The Maxus Mossy Oak Duck Blind does more than just conceal possible glare, shine and add a protective finish. It is the best camo out there, and Browning has teamed with Mossy Oak to produce the best camo finishes ever for the best firearms in the business.

The Duck Blind finish is ideal for the marsh, and that would include flooded timber, cattails, reeds, open water, jump shooting and even hunkering down against a dike among the rocks and gravel. This a light gun to carry long distances if you have to ride a bike or walk to the hunting site. It features all of the deluxe, hunter-friendly components of any Maxus model, including Invector-Plus tubes and the Lightning Trigger System. This is the gun for waterfowling, upland game or even sport shooting. The Mossy Oak Duckblind camo finish is coated with Dura-Tough Armor Coating. If you pick the shotgun up, it feels a tad sticky. Where you place your hands is pretty much where they want to stay. Not that iit is a tacky feel, but just a very sure feel. It makes the gun easier to pick up, handle, shoulder and fire. It aids in packing the gun and lessens your worries of any cosmetic damages. It provides a true outdoor-element shedding tool with a superior gripping surface.  You know you already trust the action and the workings on the inside, now trust the rugged camo-finished Maxus shotguns on the outside.

postcontent:
What you get for $1200.00
- Century Arms Polish AK-47 1960 model, New York compliant 
- 3360 rounds of Yugoslavian 7.62x39 ammo in 3 wood boxes unopened 
- Seven (7) thirty-round pre-ban magazines 
- Russian Canvas Sling for AK-47 
- Dark grey parkerized finish
- US-made milled receiver with correct selector stop
- US-made barrel (not chrome-lined)
- G2 US-made fire control group
- Slant muzzle brake – Welded for NY compliant
- Bayonet lug – removed for NY compliant
- Bayonet with sheath

About the AK-47:
This AK-47 started life as unissued Polish select-fire carbines from 1960 where they sat until Century Arms purchased them. The Polish military never issued these rifles and the parts remained unissued. Century Arms contracted the manufacture of these carbines on new milled receivers with enough US-parts to keep them 922-compliant. These are based on the real AK-47 and not the commonly-confused AKM carbines that are riveted together. 

This AK-47 was Certified by Henderson Defense Industries where I purchased it.
The rifle has only 30 rounds through it. It has sat in my safe since. It is in mint shape.

Buyer must be a holder of a NY state pistol permit or holder of any other state CCW permit or be able go through an FFL. Their FFL must accept delivery from a private individual. I need to see a copy of the buyers FFL license. Buyer pays shipping cost of rifle to FFL. Ammo and mags will be FTF.

title: For Sale:  Bersa Thunder 380 CC model - $280 or make offer
location: Reynolsburg - East of Columbus, Columbus, Ohio
postcontent: .380 acp semi-automatic pistol. Great starter pistol or for Concealed Carry. I have bought a different CC pistol and no longer need this one. This pistol is in great shape and has already been warranty repaired by Colorado Gun Works. These pistols have a factory problem of a spring jumping out the notch that is suppose to ride in and then fires erractically. CGW has machined the notch a little deeper and then inserted the spring and staked it off. Unlike a lot of other Bersa's out there, this one will now fire reliably when needed. Great pistol, just not needed anymore. Comes with factory box, key for integrated trigger lock, external trigger lock, factory test round, blackhawk holster, and factory magazine. One of the coolest features of this pistol is that fact that it is a Double Action/Single Action pistol with a De-cocker. This means you can breach a bullet into the chamber and then de-cock it. So then if you needed to defend yourself it will take a harder, safer, double action trigger pull to get the first round off. Then every round after that is single action. Love this feature. Alot of your smaller CC pistol are Double Action only, of which is not nearly as accurate as single action. Email if you would like to set up a meet to look at this pistol. Not interested in any "trades", other than firearms. No shotguns.
